        <h3>CRM Software</h3>
        <p>Manage leads, pipeline &amp; sales</p>
        <div class="pr-link">CRM Software <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></div>
      </a>
      <a href="/whatsapp-automation.html" class="p-related-card">
        <div class="pr-icon" style="background:var(--green-bg);color:#25D366"><i class="fa-brands fa-whatsapp"></i></div>
        <h3>WhatsApp Automation</h3>
        <p>Automated messaging</p>
        <div class="pr-link">WhatsApp Automation <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></div>
      </a>
      <a href="/hr-payroll.html" class="p-related-card">
        <div class="pr-icon" style="background:var(--cyan-bg);color:var(--cyan)"><i class="fa-solid fa-users"></i></div>
        <h3>HR &amp; Payroll</h3>
        <p>Employee &amp; payroll management</p>
        <div class="pr-link">HR &amp; Payroll <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="pcta">
  <div class="pcta-inner">
    <h2>Ready to Get Started?</h2>
    <p>Get a free consultation and see how our booking system can fill your calendar effortlessly.</p>
    <a href="/../#contact" class="pcta-btn"><i class="fa-solid fa-paper-plane"></i> Get Free Consultation</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="faq-section" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
  <div style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px">
    <h2 id="faq-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <p class="faq-sub">Common questions buyers ask before choosing this software.</p>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How does online booking reduce no-shows?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Automated SMS and WhatsApp reminders 24 hours and 1 hour before the appointment cut no-shows by 30 to 50 percent in our customer base. Customers can also reschedule from the reminder link without calling.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can it sync with Google Calendar and Outlook?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Two-way sync with Google Calendar, Outlook, and Apple Calendar means staff see all appointments in one place and external blocks (lunch, holidays) reflect as unavailable in booking.</div>
    </details>
